WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Hi everyone! You're listening to BigFoot Talk. With you is me, host and art director Kirill Danyukov.

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:13.000
Also joining us are BigFoot founder Proskurin Kirill and backend developer Nechaev Ivan.

3
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:21.000
Hi everyone, guys! We are very glad that you joined us. Today we'll tell you a lot of interesting things that have been on our minds.

4
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Hi everyone! I'll be happy to tell you about the technical side of our app.

5
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Before we begin, I want to express huge gratitude for your donations.

6
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:39.000
Thanks to your donations we receive our salary.

7
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Well, we should, but this young man spent it all on lapel mics at my suggestion.

8
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
No, listen, lapel mics are important. We'd be sitting here without them.

9
00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
And so your donations, your support, your warm words are always useful to us.

10
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:59.000
If you leave all of the above much more often, our team will only keep moving forward.

11
00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:07.000
Yes, that's true. Community support is priceless. It's what shows that our app is interesting.

12
00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Let's talk about our team. Who is behind our project?

13
00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:18.000
I can start with myself. I'm the team leader who brought everyone together, who guides the team forward and comes up with new ideas.

14
00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:27.000
I also work on the frontend side — that is, everything you see on the website: buttons, input fields. All of that is done by me.

15
00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:34.000
I'm responsible for the backend — the server side, database, and API.

16
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.000
And who else is on our team?

17
00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Let's start, probably, with the most important person. That's Kirill Danyukov, our art director.

18
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:46.000
It's thanks to him that you can watch our podcast and know about us.

19
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:52.000
He also makes a ton of great posts for our social media. We are very proud.

20
00:01:53.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Also on our team is Artyom Agapkin. He handles testing of our app so that you, the users, don't see any of our mistakes.

21
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:09.000
I also want to add a bit about myself: I do video editing. We also created the banner for our VK community and YouTube channel.

22
00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:15.000
We constantly exchange ideas and try to make our project better.

23
00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:19.000
Kirill, please tell us more about "Gorodskaya Legenda" (City Legend).

24
00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:24.000
"Gorodskaya Legenda" (City Legend) is a personal guide to Russian cities where routes are created by the users themselves.

25
00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:30.000
We want everyone to be able to share their favorite route and help others discover new places.

26
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:33.000
Okay, now again and without the phone.

27
00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.000
How does our app differ from others?

28
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:43.000
Our main difference is the community. Our users create the content themselves, and others follow already-made routes.

29
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:47.000
This makes the app alive and unique.

30
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:52.000
And I also want to announce that this month the alpha version of the app will be released.

31
00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:55.000
And each of you can try it out.

32
00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:01.000
Ivan, please tell us more about the technical side. How are you developing the backend?

33
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:07.000
We are using Django and its library for creating APIs.

34
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:16.000
In the alpha version there will be no backend. We will use a temporary solution on Firebase to launch testing faster.

35
00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Yes, but the full backend will appear in the beta.

36
00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:29.000
So the database will initially be on SQLite, right? Correct, Ivan — SQLite.

37
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:34.000
And the mobile app release will use Firebase.

38
00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.000
Great, thank you for adding that, Ivan.

39
00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:42.000
Well, of course I'm adding to it — it's my part after all.

40
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:49.000
Django is a proven solution that we use in our personal projects.

41
00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Since we want our app to be developed with confidence, we are using exactly this stack.

42
00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:03.000
Interesting — so right now the most important thing is to test the app, and only then scale it up, right?

43
00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:10.000
Yes, that's right. We try to do everything step by step so the app works without failures.

44
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:13.440
Guys, what are your plans for the future?

45
00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:17.080
Our plans are grand. After releasing the alpha version

46
00:04:17.080 --> 00:04:19.840
we will release the beta version, as we mentioned above.

47
00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:22.880
And then we will promote more actively —

48
00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:25.840
that is, possibly buying ads from other bloggers

49
00:04:25.840 --> 00:04:28.760
or on targeted platforms like VK or Yandex.

50
00:04:28.760 --> 00:04:32.160
We will fully expand so that BigFoot

51
00:04:32.160 --> 00:04:35.120
and Gorodskaya Legenda are known not only in Tambov Oblast

52
00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:36.680
and nearby cities,

53
00:04:36.680 --> 00:04:40.360
but also by a larger population across the CIS.

54
00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:44.640
We also want to create personal routes so that

55
00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:47.520
cities can be explored solo.

56
00:04:47.520 --> 00:04:48.520
Yes, great.

57
00:04:48.520 --> 00:04:52.600
But what else would I add? We need monetization for our community.

58
00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:56.360
We want to enable monetization on Dzen, VK, and YouTube.

59
00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:59.760
And we will probably set up a Boosty in the future.

60
00:04:59.760 --> 00:05:03.760
Well, our episode is coming to an end. Let's wrap up.

61
00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:06.480
So, to sum up, I've introduced you more closely to my team.

62
00:05:06.480 --> 00:05:10.760
We covered what Gorodskaya Legenda is and what it's for.

63
00:05:10.760 --> 00:05:14.320
And with the development plan laid out, you've gotten much closer to us.

64
00:05:14.320 --> 00:05:16.720
Thank you all for that.

65
00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:19.760
We keep working and delighting you with new features.

66
00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:28.440
I'm Kirill Proskurin.

67
00:05:28.440 --> 00:05:31.360
I can say.. no, never mind, let's redo it.

68
00:05:31.360 --> 00:05:33.360
I'm responsible for the backend.

69
00:05:33.360 --> 00:05:37.320
This.. again, I'll go again.

70
00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:42.000
Buddy, please tell us about… (censored)

71
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:43.000
Buddy.

72
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.320
Ivan, please tell us about…

73
00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:56.160
(humming)

74
00:05:56.160 --> 00:05:57.160
We'll put these in as bloopers at the end.

75
00:05:58.160 --> 00:06:00.160
Alright, okay, plans for the future.

76
00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:02.160
So what are our plans for the future?

77
00:06:12.160 --> 00:06:13.160
Open the door.

78
00:06:13.160 --> 00:06:14.160
What?

79
00:06:14.160 --> 00:06:16.160
We'll definitely make clips.

80
00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:19.160
And post ones where there's no swearing.

81
00:06:19.160 --> 00:06:28.120
What does one iceberg say to another when it's feeling down?

82
00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:37.120
Don't crack up.

83
00:06:37.120 --> 00:06:41.120
And now you'll see a sketch: Nurlan Saburov (a Kazakh stand-up comedian) lays tiles.

84
00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:45.120
Or a deleted scene from the movie "Joker 2."

85
00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:48.120
And there's also something I'd like to clarify.

86
00:06:48.120 --> 00:06:49.120
This is Zakir.

87
00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:51.120
Thank you.

88
00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:54.120
Also a joke.

89
00:06:54.120 --> 00:06:58.120
A child asks their friend:

90
00:06:58.120 --> 00:07:00.120
Who is your father?

91
00:07:00.120 --> 00:07:02.120
The second one answers: my father is Michael Jackson.

92
00:07:02.120 --> 00:07:03.120
The first one says: "Prove it."

93
00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:06.120
The second one wipes his face and turned from black to white.

94
00:07:06.120 --> 00:07:10.120
Let me tell you a joke about a boy who always borrowed a desk.

95
00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:12.120
for 5 minutes, who…

96
00:07:12.120 --> 00:07:14.120
No, no, no, no, no, no.

97
00:07:20.120 --> 00:07:24.120
For your attention: a snail has run out of slime.
